caption: Loved the live music! Restaurant looks welcoming and the food and drinks were decent. However, service was not good. At the beginning of the evening everything was fine, but when it’s started to get busier things got a little... sloppy. Staff needs to step up their game.

My husband and I helped set up a wedding reception last night and I cannot rave about the staff enough! The entire staff and management were friendly, attentive and incredibly helpful. Any issue or item I needed was resolved/found quickly.  When the food and drink started flowing the guests were treated to delicious food and the wait staff kept the cocktails coming to the tables at the perfect pace.  The space was absolutely perfect for the covid-friendly reception and we will definitely return for a date night dinner!

Start up with an ice, cold, well served “caña” (Estrella Galica)..Jorge was great without saying anything he already knew what I wanted : Pulpo la Gallega ! I also ordered patatas bravas. The service was prompt without rushing ..only 4 tables outside so space is limited. Inside to my like felt cold, needed some “love” candles, music..missing “warmth” I understand also it was a Thursday still could improve the mood...the octopus was great, “en su punto”, tender, cooked just right, potatoes a bit over cooked but tasty, cover by olive oil and “paprika” (wished they used pimentón de la Vera) content. The “Patatas Bravas” were fine, a bit too sweet for me but with a little salt I enjoy them..Viva España 🇪🇸

The atmosphere and staff were fine and Jorge was exceptional. But the food was not what we expected, maybe our standards are to high after living in San Sebastián Spain for 2 years but nothing was not prepared well at all. We started with pimentos del piqullio that was supposed to hot and it was cold and there was more croqueta (flour) and no seafood at all with no flavor. Our main dishes were just as bad my Mariscada was flavorless, and my wife’s Pescado al Limón was the same and it was stuffed with flour instead of seafood, I think she found a piece of shrimp mixed in with the flour. I guess if you never had authentic Spanish (European) food I guess this place would be ok.

I give it a 4 because the food was great, live music awesome but the waiter Gabriel was awful.  Other people were getting there food way before us.  These are people that just there.  Took forever just to bring over Sangria.  He was always saying that it's the kitchens fault or the bars fault that it was late.  Excuses, excuses, excuses.  Never even want to see that guy again. I went there Feb 6 2021. The live music was great. The food excellent but the service provided by the server was the worst I have experience in a very long time. 1st very late bringing the sangria and the appetizers. Then he took our order including a pitcher of sangria. Never brought out the salad until we asked for it. Then he brought (salad) it with our main meal, one person at time. The pitcher of sangria arrived after we all finished our meals. Didn't bring out the bread that it's included in the meals until it was mentioned again. My order was brought incorrectly I asked for fresh vegetables and brought out rice instead. What was the worst is him blaming everyone else (kitchen & bar staff) for his lack of service. He would say things like they ran out of bread and sangria yet other servers would bring those items to other customers. I watched how other parties would come order eat and leave and we haven't even gotten our appetizers. Again bad service from the server. His name is Gabriel

My family goes out to eat there all the time, this was mine and my fiancé’s first time and we were so impressed I highly recommend for dinner and I especially recommend for your events!! The restaurant is beautiful, food was Good! However, the server complaint last night that he wasn’t working there since few months ago and he was doing just a favor for New Year’s Eve, half of the menu wasn’t available at the time we ordered(8:00 pm), Why such a good restaurant didn’t have all the items available for an important night, knowing they will Be busy? Unfortunately the flamenco show was good, but we were not informed by the hostess that we had to pay 15 P/P for the show while we were eating, It was not way to avoid the show, so we end up paying regardless, would be better if we were informed a head of time. After all when the time for dessert came, We were told that the cheesecake was gone because other server took the last  piece making our server to have a hard time. ( I don’t care the excuses I just want to have what I want) restaurant was not ready for New Year’s Eve. Also I’m kind of glad I don’t have the cheesecake because the server said the cheesecake was made by the owner and “ who knows what Kind of recipe they follow; it is better not to try! All the tables had bread to start the night, as we had to ask for it, no straws available with the water, and the Pitcher of Sangria was crack halfway! I feel disappointed big time, by the restaurant and service! I was hoping for an excellent night; we just received inferior service and a poor attitude. Hopefully, in 2021, they do better!

Stay away from this place. The prices are insane and the food is not original. Meaning, nothing is Spain's products. Example. $14 for (Serrano Ham) and Manchego cheese. What they call Serrano Spanish Ham, is the same cheap Serrano dry ham that you buy at Walmart. Has nothing to do with the original Spanish Serrano from Spain. The Paella Valencia was $22 and rest assure that is not paella. It was yellow rice with seafood thrown in there which was not even fresh. On top of that, they have a guy playing guitar which doesn't even interact with the public what so ever and has a face that you can tell he hates his job.  To the point that ones he's done no one even claps. That's how sad it is. In addition to our waitress been so lost and disoriented that you could tell he never worked in a restaurant in his life. After been there for 45 min he comes with the bread and then asks if we would like the appetizer first. It's an appetizer dude, of course, we wanted first.  This restaurant is stealing money from customers left and right. Am originally from Spain and I've been to many Spanish Restaurants, this is not Spain food people. The owner of this place seriously needs to consider hiring a new chef or looking for a different business because this one is going downhill soon.

I'm going to give this location the 3 star rating, because of the price mostly. Lunch was about 11 dollars and change which doesn't include a beverage, and the quality of the food wasn't worth that much for lunch. A typical lunch in downtown Tampa should be in the 7 or 8 dollar range (based on me working downtown for 6 years). The location inside is actually quite nice an all white dining area with white chairs, the place does look a bit classy, but the food is just decent not bad, but not good enough to tell people about and recommend the joint. If you are looking for something different I wouldn't tell you not to go there, but expect an average meal for an above average price. They do have a couple of dishes that are pretty good (pulled pork) they don't include the stuffed white fish and the, fried palinoma steak. I probably visit this place once a year after I'm tired of repeating everything else.

They accommodated 2 VERY LARGE high school drama troupes during our State Festival and the food was spectacular! Fantastic pork that was amazingly tender, lovely, flavorful fish that flaked so nicely... and the plantains. WOW. LOVED IT! But the leche flan was the show stopper. I’m picky about my flan, being of Castilian descent. This was a beautiful flan with a generous sauce underneath.  My Mama would be proud of this flan! They fresh prep all their food, and it’s obvious. Feeding 50 of us cafeteria style is tough. Pleasing teenagers is tough. They succeeded in spades. What’s more... they were pleasant, kind, and had even a marvelous conga & steel acoustic guitar duo entertaining us all evening. Nicola and Roberto were fabulous! Of special note, one of my students had a terrible cold & I asked if they would send us back to the hotel with a bit of salt so she could gargle with salt water. Alfredo, the owner, gave me a nice large cup of sea salt to bring back with us. What a kind soul.

We were looking for somewhere to eat tapas and luckily for us, we came across Spain restaurant and Toma bar!  It was happy hour, 4-7, and we were hungry...and thirsty!  We went in and were greeted by the friendly bartender, Alex R.  He offered to make me a mojito and it was oh so delicious!  Apparently he makes the best mojitos in town so don't forget to ask for him by name! ;)  (His sangrias are good too!)The tapas were yummy and so pretty.  I've always believed that you eat first with your eyes and everything looked good enough to eat!  It was all fresh made and piping hot and very tasty!  The prices are reasonable and the portions are fair.  The atmosphere is very relaxing so come in and sit at the bar or grab a table!
